  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lesotho Homes with Urban Gardens (HUG) Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Poor Urban Households</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The HUG Project will work with poor urban households to increase their skills and productive assets in terms of home gardens for the production of vegetable crops for household consumption and localised sales.  These gardens will assist households to offset their proportion of income dedicated to the increasing food commodity prices, while providing a secondary source of income for targeted households.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project is intended to mitigate the impact of rising food prices by increasing household access to fresh vegetables produced in home gardens. CRS will apply its extensive experience in designing and implementing homestead garden activities in rural communities, adopting proven techniques and methods to urban settings while using existing monitoring and evaluation expertise to measure impact and document lessons learned.</narrative>
  </description>
